High-Level Design (HLD)
1. Overview
The Basic Parking System is a RESTful Spring Boot application that manages parking floors, spots, and vehicles. It supports parking and unparking vehicles, and can be extended for more features.
2. Main Components
Controller Layer: Exposes REST APIs for parking operations.
Service Layer: Contains business logic for parking/unparking and lot management.
Strategy Layer: Implements parking spot allocation strategies.
Model Layer: Contains domain objects (Vehicle, ParkingSpot, ParkingFloor, VehicleType).
3. Key Flows
Initialize Lot: Create floors and spots with types.
Park Vehicle: Find a suitable spot and generate a ticket.
Unpark Vehicle: Free the spot using the ticket.

Low-Level Design (LLD)
1. Model Layer
Vehicle
Fields: regNumber, color, type (VehicleType)
VehicleType
Enum: CAR, BIKE, TRUCK
ParkingSpot
Fields: spotId, floorNumber, supportedType, isFree, parkedVehicle
Methods: park(Vehicle), unpark(), isFree()
ParkingFloor
Fields: floorNum, List<parkingspot></parkingspot>
Constructor: Initializes spots with types
2. Service Layer
ParkingService
Fields: List<parkingfloor>, ParkingStrategy, ReentrantLock</parkingfloor>
Methods:
createLot(int floors, int spotsPerFloor)
park(Vehicle): Finds spot, parks vehicle, returns ticket
unpark(String ticket): Frees spot using ticket
3. Strategy Layer
ParkingStrategy (interface)
Methods:
findSpot(List<parkingfloor>, VehicleType): Finds available spot for type</parkingfloor>
findSpotId(List<parkingfloor>, String spotId): Finds spot by ID</parkingfloor>
FloorStrategyImpl
Implements ParkingStrategy
Logic for finding/freeing spots
4. Controller Layer
ParkingController
Endpoints:
POST /parking/init: Initialize lot
POST /parking/park: Park vehicle
(Extendable for /unpark)

Relationships
ParkingController → ParkingService → ParkingStrategy → ParkingFloor → ParkingSpot
VehicleType is used by Vehicle and ParkingSpot


